[Korea's high alertness and intensive surveillance activities are
reflected by the detection of additional outbreaks, one of which was
reportedly already confirmed as HPAI H5N1 while the other one might
be of lower pathogenicity (LPAI). Ruling out high pathogenicity
(HPAI, which is OIE-notifiable) is dependent upon lab results.
In the meantime, Korea has officially confirmed, in a notification to
the OIE, its H5N1 outbreak; see
<http://www.oie.int/Messages/061128KOR.htm>. - Mod.AS]
